%% vLLM CPU - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as KServe Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant API as vLLM API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Engine as AsyncLLM Engine<br/>(in-process)
    participant CPU as CPU Backend<br/>(PagedAttention)
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GRPC as vLLM gRPC Server<br/>50051/TCP gRPC
    participant Router as Rust Router<br/>(llm-d)

    Note over API,S3: Flow 1: Model Loading at Startup
    API->>Engine: Initialize engine
    Engine->>HF: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: HF Token (optional)
    HF-->>Engine: Model artifacts
    Engine->>S3: OR download from S3<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>Engine: Model artifacts
    Engine->>Engine: Load to local filesystem

    Note over Client,CPU: Flow 2: OpenAI-Compatible Inference Request
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / None
    Gateway->>API: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8000, plaintext (cluster-internal)<br/>Auth: API Key (optional)
    API->>Engine: Submit inference request<br/>(in-process call)
    Engine->>CPU: PagedAttention compute<br/>(in-process)
    CPU-->>Engine: Token output
    Engine-->>API: Streaming/complete response
    API-->>Gateway: JSON Response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Router,CPU: Flow 3: gRPC Engine Communication
    Router->>GRPC: VllmEngine.Generate<br/>gRPC/HTTP2 50051/TCP<br/>plaintext, no auth
    GRPC->>Engine: Submit request<br/>(in-process)
    Engine->>CPU: Compute
    CPU-->>Engine: Result
    Engine-->>GRPC: Streaming response
    GRPC-->>Router: gRPC stream
